<TITLE> Foreign chamber presses for Sat-Sun weekend </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 19 (bdnews24.com)The Foreign Investors Chamber of Commerce and Industry on Sunday pressed the government to shift the weekend from Friday-Saturday to Saturday-Sunday to boost the country's economic development. "Friday should be a working day to keep pace with the modern world, and so Saturday and Sunday should constitute the weekend," FICCI president Waliur Rahman Bhuiyan said at a programme at the Radisson Hotel. Bhuiyan, a leading businessman, said an improvement in the country's law and order situation and better electricity supplies remained vital to speedier economic development. He also said recent government proposals to maintain state-owned factories were short-sighted. "The government should not do business, governments should create scope for business and provide assistance to the private sector," said Bhuiyan. Also attending the programme, industries minister Dilip Barua said privatisation initiatives in Bangladesh had not fared well in the past. b
